{
  "texts": [
    "In the LLM domain, this approach is known as few-shot prompting, and it is widely used to improve the output of LLMs [11].",
    "The main components of ADL-LLMIn the following, we describe the main modules of ADL-LLM, i.e., those used both in the zero-shot and the few-shot modalities.",
    "Sensor States Generation.The smart home generates a continuous stream of binary sensor events 𝑆𝑡𝑟𝑒𝑎𝑚 = ⟨..., 𝐸 𝑆 𝑙 𝑡 -1, 𝐸 𝑆 𝑚 𝑡, 𝐸 𝑆 𝑞 𝑡 +1,... ⟩.",
    "Each 𝐸 𝑆 𝑡 represents the activation or the deactivation of a sensor 𝑆 at a specific time 𝑡.",
    "For instance, consider a magnetic sensor on the fridge."
  ]
}